<p><strong>How to Create and Activate a New CERS Business User Account:</strong></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Open your web browser and navigate to the CERS Central page. (<a href="http://cers.calepa.ca.gov">http://cers.calepa.ca.gov</a>)</li>
<li>Select the &ldquo;Business Portal Sign In&rdquo; link from the top of the CERS Central page.</li>
<li>Select the &ldquo;Create New Account&rdquo; button, located below the &ldquo;New to CERS?&rdquo; section of the CERS Business Sign In page.</li>
<li>After completing the web form, select the &ldquo;Create My Account&rdquo; button.</li>
<li>You will then receive an e-mail notification, from CERS, containing an Account Activation Link. Open the link provided in the e-mail message to activate your CERS Business user account.</li>
<li>Once your account has been activated, you can then return to the CERS Business Sign In page and sign-in to CERS Business, using your username and password.</li>
</ol>